message.entry: First input to a multilayer map must be a string array, cell array of character vectors, or cell array of map layer object.
Layer ''{0}'' is not compatible with the first layer, ''{1}''. All the map layer objects must have the same size, resolution, and location in the world.
{0} must be a cell array of scalars with length equal to number of layers.
{0} must be a cell array of length equal to number of layers.
{0} must be a cell array of length equal to the number of layer names. Matrices must be numeric or logical and their size must match in the first two dimensions.
CellDataSize must either be a numeric array or a cell array whose size matches the number of layers, {0}.
Map layer ''{0}'' exists in another multiLayerMap object. Copy the mapLayer object or remove from existing multilayer map.
